# =============================================
# MESSAGING SYSTEM CONFIGURATION
# =============================================

# Message Processor
# Enable automatic message processing in browser context
# Set to 'true' to auto-start processor when app loads
# Recommended: 'false' (start manually via UI)
VITE_MESSAGE_PROCESSOR_AUTO_START=false

# WA-HA Configuration (WhatsApp HTTP API)
# These are loaded from database, but can be set here for initial setup
# VITE_WAHA_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
# VITE_WAHA_SESSION_NAME=default
# VITE_WAHA_TOKEN=your-secret-token-here

# Message Processing Intervals (milliseconds)
# VITE_MESSAGE_PROCESS_INTERVAL=30000  # 30 seconds
# VITE_HEALTH_CHECK_INTERVAL=300000    # 5 minutes

# Retry Configuration
# VITE_MESSAGE_MAX_ATTEMPTS=3
# VITE_MESSAGE_RETRY_DELAY=300  # seconds (5 minutes)

# Debug Mode
# Enable detailed logging for messaging system
# VITE_MESSAGING_DEBUG=false

# =============================================
# USAGE NOTES
# =============================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp .env.example .env

# 2. Configure WA-HA in database:
#    Run: supabase/migrations/20260219140000_messaging_seed.sql
#    Update: messaging_providers.config with your WA-HA credentials

# 3. Start message processor:
#    - Via UI: Admin Panel > Provedores > Iniciar Processador
#    - Via Code: messageProcessor.start()
#    - Auto-start: Set VITE_MESSAGE_PROCESSOR_AUTO_START=true

# 4. Monitor health:
#    - UI: Admin Panel > Status dos Provedores
#    - Database: SELECT * FROM provider_health_logs ORDER BY created_at DESC

# 5. View messages:
#    - UI: Quotation Detail > Aba Mensagens
#    - Database: SELECT * FROM quotation_messages WHERE quotation_id = '...'

# =============================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================

# Issue: Messages stuck in 'pending'
# Solution: Check if MessageProcessor is running. Start it manually.

# Issue: All messages fail with network error
# Solution: Verify WA-HA container is running (docker ps)
#          Check apiUrl in messaging_providers.config

# Issue: Session validation fails
# Solution: Check WA-HA session status: GET http://localhost:3000/sessions
#          Scan QR code to authenticate WhatsApp

# Issue: Health checks show 'unhealthy'
# Solution: Restart WA-HA container: docker restart waha
#          Check provider_health_logs for detailed error

# =============================================
# PRODUCTION RECOMMENDATIONS
# =============================================

# 1. Use environment-specific configuration
# 2. Encrypt sensitive data in messaging_providers.config
# 3. Set up monitoring alerts for failed messages
# 4. Run MessageProcessor as separate service (not in browser)
# 5. Implement rate limiting (already in code via delay)
# 6. Set up backup providers (primary + fallback)
# 7. Regular backup of quotation_messages table
# 8. Monitor provider_health_logs for degradation patterns
